        <definition id="import-auto-id2929815"><term>accommodation</term> <meaning id="fs-id2408874">the ability of the eye to adjust its focal length is known as accommodation</meaning></definition>
            <definition id="import-auto-id1435993"><term>presbyopia</term> <meaning id="fs-id3163182">a condition in which the lens of the eye becomes progressively unable to focus on objects close to the viewer</meaning></definition>
